    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="995"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d995">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 70.3.3212/10b.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister in charge of American interests in
                            Mexico</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 28, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>After consultation with Brazilian Ambassador here, it was agreed that this
                    Department would communicate directly with you and that you would reply through
                    your Embassy in this city.</p>
                <p>You are authorized to use the 2000 pesos left by the American Chargé and to draw
                    upon this Department for such other funds as you may require.</p>
                <p>Your Ambassador here called attention to the fact that the American Embassy
                    having been formally placed in charge of the British Minister could not be
                    delivered over to you without specific instructions. The matter has been brought
                    to the attention of the British Ambassador and he will communicate with the
                    British Minister in Mexico.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
